quran[15]{c,v,t,f}:
  15,1,"Alif Lām Ra<sup>1</sup>. These are the verses of the Book and a clear Qur’an.","[1] See footnote 2:1."
  15,2,"The disbelievers will soon<sup>2</sup> wish that they were Muslims.","[2] On the Judgment Day or upon their death."
  15,3,"Let them eat and enjoy themselves and be diverted with false hope; they will come to know.",""
  15,4,"We never destroyed any town except that it had a destined time.",""
  15,5,"No nation can advance its appointed time, nor can they delay it.",""
  15,6,"They say, “O you to whom the Reminder has been sent down, You are surely insane<sup>3</sup>!","[3] These deriding remarks were very hard on the Prophet (ﷺ), and Allah consoles him in this surah."
  15,7,"Why do you not bring us the angels, if you are truthful?”",""
  15,8,"We do not send down the angels except for a just cause, and then [the disbelievers] would be granted no respite<sup>4</sup>.","[4] i.e., then they would be destroyed on the spot."
  15,9,"It is We Who have sent down the Reminder<sup>5</sup>, and it is We Who will preserve it<sup>6</sup>.","[5] As a reminder for people.\n [6] From distortion, alteration, addition, and omission. More than 1400 years have elapsed and not a single word of this Qur’an has been changed, although enemies have tried their utmost."
  15,10,"We did send messengers before you among the factions of early peoples.",""
  15,11,"No messenger came to them except that they ridiculed him.",""
  15,12,"This is how We let this [denial] enter the hearts of the wicked<sup>7</sup>.","[7] For they rebelled against the Truth and did not submit to it."
  15,13,"They will not believe in it, although the examples of the earlier people are well established.",""
  15,14,"Even if We were to open for them a gateway to the heaven, through which they kept ascending,",""
  15,15,"they would still say, “Our eyes have been dazzled; rather, we have been bewitched.”",""
